<TITLE> 'Hundreds of homes' razed in Dhaka slum blaze </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 18 (bdnews24.com)Fire swept through a Dhaka slum in the early hours of Thursday, razing hundreds of dwellings within half an hour, witnesses said. The blaze broke out at the Bashbaria slum in Mohammadpur around midnight, rescue workers said. It was under control about 40 minutes later, but not before it had gutted "almost three quarters of the homes", said one witness at the scene. "You can't imagine the devastation in such a short time," he said
